"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:4.4.7\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">4.4.7</span> Censer</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מִקְטֶרֶת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(miqtereth)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:19\">2CH 26:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:11\">EZK 8:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">θυΐσκη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(thuiskē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc1:22\">1MA 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd2:9\">1ES 2:9</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">θυμιατήριον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(thumiatērion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc7:11\">4MA 7:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">λιβανωτός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(libanōtos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:3\">REV 8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:5\">REV 8:5</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">πυρεῖον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pureion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir50:9\">SIR 50:9</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/PTZ-0081_censer_firepan.jpg\" alt=\"Terracotta censer for burning incense and firepan for moving hot coals\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Terracotta censer for burning incense and firepan for moving hot coals (© Ray Pritz by United Bible Societies)</figcaption></figure>The censer was a small bowl or pan in which incense was burned. It was usually made of metal. It had a handle so that the priest could hold it and carry it to the altar.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Coals, usually from the altar, were placed into the bowl or flat pan. On top of these coals was sprinkled a small amount of incense, which gave off a pleasant smell when it was burned by the coals.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Some cultures will be familiar with burning incense in religious ceremonies, and there may be a special word for the instrument in which this is done. However, translators should be careful not to choose a word that is associated only with the rites of cultic or non-Christian worship. It may be necessary to expand the expression by saying “small pan for burning sweet-smelling perfume.” See also <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.2.4 Incense altar&lt;REALIA:4.2.4&gt;</a> and <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.4.5 Small shovel, firepan&lt;REALIA:4.4.5&gt;</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
